The idea of making a pure throwback record left #PeteWentz with a bad taste in his mouth. “Whenever artists I love say that something is a ‘return to form,’ I’m like, ughhhh,” the #FallOutBoy bassist says. “People think they want that, but if we do it, you won’t like it. And it’ll feel inauthentic.” At the link in bio, our March 2023 cover star @petewentz explains why in some ways, “So Much (for) Stardust” splits the difference.

Introducing the Pete Wentz Artist Series StingRay.
As the bassist and co-founder of Fall Out Boy, @petewentz has shaped the sound of pop punk, emo and beyond. Now, as a part of the Ernie Ball Music Man family, he's forging a new path for the StingRay with @sterlingbymusicman's first full-scale passive bass. In Pete's words, it's "simple, quality, well-crafted, and it looks pretty cool." Available in Black or Fiesta Red.
Europe so far photos @elliottxingham

In partnership with @altpress, we're making @petewentz's Artist Series StingRay bass available in the tour-tested Fiesta Red finish. Get exclusive early access to this finish – in limited quantities – available for pre-order over on @altpress's website now.

📷 Elliott Ingham
Have been working on this for over a year. Excited to have my first @sterlingbymusicman signature bass out in the world 🦆🦆🦆 (need that loon emoji)
